Package edu.ncsu.csc216.packdoption.util

Interface SortedList<E extends Comparable<E>>

Type Parameters:
E - The object element the client works with when constructing the Generic ArrayList
All Known Implementing Classes:
SortedLinkedList
public interface SortedList<E extends Comparable<E>>
This interface is a subset of the java.util.List interface and requires that elements be stored in sorted order based on Comparable. No duplicate items. This interface is adapted from java.util.List.
Since:
1.2
Author:
Jessica Young Schmidt, David R. Wright An ordered collection (also known as a sequence). The user of this interface has precise control over where in the list each element is inserted. The user can access elements by their integer index (position in the list), and search for elements in the list., Josh Bloch, Neal Gafter
